  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "If my ATM card is blocked for online transactions then how do i restart it?",
  "response": "If your ATM card is blocked for online transactions, you'll need to take specific steps to unblock or reactivate it. Here's a general guide to help you restart your card's online transaction capabilities:\n\n1. **Understand Why Your Card Was Blocked:**\n   - **Multiple Failed Attempts:** Entering the wrong PIN too many times can block your card.\n   - **Suspicious Activity:** Unusual transactions may trigger a security block.\n   - **Expiration or Renewal Issues:** Sometimes, cards are temporarily blocked during renewal.\n\n2. **Contact Your Bank:**\n   - **Customer Support Hotline:** Call the customer service number provided by your bank. This number is usually found on the back of your ATM card or on the bank\u2019s official website.\n   - **Visit a Branch:** Go to your nearest bank branch and speak with a representative. Bring identification (like your ID card or passport) and any relevant account information.\n   - **Use Online Messaging:** Some banks offer live chat or secure messaging through their online banking portals or mobile apps.\n\n3. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - Be prepared to answer security questions or provide identification to confirm your identity. This step is crucial to protect your account from unauthorized access.\n\n4. **Request Unblocking or Reactivation:**\n   - **Customer Service:** Ask the representative to unblock your card for online transactions. They may do this immediately or guide you through the necessary steps.\n   - **Update Information:** If the block was due to outdated information, ensure all your details (like contact information) are current.\n\n5. **Set or Reset Your PIN (if necessary):**\n   - Sometimes, resetting your PIN can help in unblocking the card. Follow the bank\u2019s instructions to create a new PIN securely.\n\n6. **Enable Online Transactions:**\n   - **Through Mobile App or Online Banking:** Some banks allow you to manage your card settings directly through their digital platforms. Log in to your account and look for options related to card management or security settings.\n   - **Check Transaction Limits:** Ensure that your online transaction limits are set according to your needs. Adjust them if necessary through customer service or online settings.\n\n7. **Confirm Reactivation:**\n   - Once unblocked, try making a small online transaction to ensure that your card is active and functioning correctly.\n\n8. **Enhance Security:**\n   - **Monitor Your Account:** Regularly check your account for any unauthorized transactions.\n   - **Update Passwords:** If you suspect any security issues, update your online banking passwords and security questions.\n   - **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):** If your bank offers 2FA, enabling it can add an extra layer of security to your online transactions.\n\n9. **Prevent Future Blocks:**\n   - **Use Correct Information:** Always enter the correct PIN and follow security protocols.\n   - **Stay Informed:** Keep your contact information up-to-date with your bank to receive alerts and notifications about your account activity.\n\n**Note:** The exact process may vary depending on your bank's policies and the reason your card was blocked. Always follow the specific instructions provided by your financial institution.\n\nIf you continue to experience issues after following these steps, consider requesting a new card from your bank to ensure uninterrupted access to your online transactions.",
